ls  Acquiring knowledge across several fields helps students formulate solutions to new and complex problems in the context of current social and economic considerations Apply now GETTING STARTED Graduate Student Handbook Graduate Student Handbook Important Dates and Deadlines for Graduate Students Important Dates and Deadlines for Graduate Students Fellowships  DEGREE REQUIREMENTS I  CIVIL ENGINEERING MS Thesis Non Thesis In addition to the Graduate College minimum requirements  students must meet the following program requirements  Graduate College    credit hours are required to graduate Minimum of    credits of  XX level courses    credits must be from CME  XX courses  excludes CME       must be CME  XX or COE  XX course  excludes CME     or equivalent Remaining    credits hours  Must be CME  XX  XX or COE  XX  XX  Only one CME     or its equivalent is accepted for graduation credit  CME     or its equivalent will not count for graduation credit ENGR  XX are not accepted Any course outside the COE must be approved by academic adviser first    credit hours are required to graduate Minimum of    credit hours of coursework needed besides thesis  Minimum of    credits of  XX level courses    credits must be from CME  XX courses  excludes CME       credits must be CME  XX or COE  XX course  excludes CME     or equivalent Remaining    credit hours  Must be CME  XX  XX or COE  XX  XX  Only one CME     or its equivalent is accepted for graduation credit  CME     or its equivalent will not count for graduation credit ENGR  XX are not accepted Any course outside the COE must be approved by academic adviser first Minimum of    credits of CME      MS Thesis PhD In addition to the Graduate College minimum requirements  students must meet the following program requirements  Graduate College     credit hours are required to graduate Minimum of    credit hours of coursework needed besides dissertation     credit hours will be granted towards coursework credits from MS degree Re